 {"id": "franken_networkx-tuttesig", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] tutte_polynomial signature required positional x,y; nx takes only G", "description": "nx.tutte_polynomial(G) returns a symbolic sympy polynomial in x, y. fnx's wrapper required numeric positional arguments ``tutte_polynomial(G, x, y)`` and evaluated the polynomial at that point, so drop-in calls like ``nx.tutte_polynomial(G)`` raised TypeError('missing 2 required positional arguments: x and y'). Made x, y default to None. When both are None, delegate to nx (returns sympy polynomial; raises ModuleNotFoundError if sympy unavailable, matching nx's behaviour). When both are provided, keep fnx's numeric deletion-contraction evaluator as an extension. Partial args (only one of x, y) now raise TypeError with a clear message.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T20:00:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T20:00:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T20:00:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Default x=y=None; delegate to nx for symbolic; retain numeric extension", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-mstweightwrong", "title": "REVIEW: [CRITICAL] minimum/maximum_spanning_tree returned suboptimal (non-minimum/maximum) trees on weighted graphs", "description": "The Rust Kruskal implementation returned wrong spanning trees on weighted graphs with certain edge-insertion patterns. On cycle_graph(5) with weights abs(u-v)+1 (giving 4 edges of weight 2 plus one edge of weight 5), fnx returned a tree with total weight 11 (including the weight-5 edge) where nx correctly returned weight 8 (picking all four weight-2 edges). Manual construction of the same edges sometimes worked, sometimes didn't \u2014 the Rust edge-iteration order appears to not be strictly sorted by weight in all cases, so Kruskal picked edges in the wrong order. Added _mst_has_weight_edge_attr helper; when any edge carries the named weight attribute, delegate to nx for the entire MST / spanning-edges computation. Unweighted graphs still hit the Rust fast path.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T20:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T20:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T20:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate to nx when any edge carries weight attr", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-mstcallable", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] minimum/maximum_spanning_tree rejected callable weight with TypeError", "description": "nx accepts ``weight`` as either a string attribute key or a callable ``weight(u, v, d) -> float``. The Rust binding was strictly typed to str and raised TypeError('argument weight: function object is not an instance of str') on callable weight inputs. Gate the Rust fast path on ``isinstance(weight, str)``; non-str (callable) cases delegate to nx \u2014 also for minimum_spanning_edges and maximum_spanning_edges wrappers.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T20:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T20:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T20:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate callable weight to nx", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-simrankvals", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] simrank_similarity returned different scores than nx at tight tolerance", "description": "The Rust simrank_similarity_rust gave numerically different SimRank scores than nx on karate_club_graph. Diffs of ~0.5-8% across tested node pairs, persistent across max_iterations in {100, 1000} and tolerance in {1e-4, 1e-9} \u2014 so it's an algorithmic mismatch (likely a different iteration formulation than nx's matrix update) rather than a convergence issue. Delegated to nx via a private _simrank_impl helper so scores match exactly. NodeNotFound validation for missing source/target is still performed locally.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T21:00:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T21:00:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T21:00:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate to nx for exact parity", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
